==English==

===Adjective===
'''enciente'''

# pregnant, expecting a baby.
#:'' She was found guilty, but sentence was delayed, as her counsel said that she was enciente. ''

====References====
#The Reign of Henry the Eighth, Volume 1 (of 3), by James Anthony Froude, et al - first published 1909, London & Toronto J.M. Dent & Sons Ltd. New York E.P. Dutton & Co ''And the time was pressing, for the new queen was enciente, and further concealment was not to be thought of. ''